article:
The United States Office of Management and Budget (OMB) has defined 381
Metropolitan Statistical Areas (MSAs) for the United States and seven for Puerto
Rico. The OMB defines a Metropolitan Statistical Area
as one or more adjacent counties or county equivalents that have at least one
urban core area of at least 50,000 population, plus adjacent territory that has
a high degree of social and economic integration with the core as measured by
commuting ties. __TOC__
